House Resolution 362
By: Representative Mitchell of the 88th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 20, 2025, as Girls Empowerment Day; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Trinity Girls Network, founded in July 2016 by Outstanding Georgia Citizen
3 Award winner Dr. Jacqueline Mohair, persistently works toward the empowerment of girls
4 and young women through a three-pronged approach: ending violence against girls and
5 women, preparing girls for success, and providing opportunities through education; and
6 WHEREAS, Trinity Girls Network extends its impact internationally, including through its
7 efforts in Zambia, where it provides critical support such as food, clothing, and toys to girls
8 in need, furthering its mission to empower and uplift; and
9 WHEREAS, Trinity Girls Network operates as a non-governmental organization with
10 consultative status under the United Nations Economic and Social Council, allowing it to
11 advocate for the rights and empowerment of women and girls on a global stage and aligning
12 its work with the United Nations' Sustainable Development Goals; and
13 WHEREAS, globally, 65 million girls and young women are not in school, 31 million girls
14 of primary school age are not in school, and 33 million fewer girls than boys attend primary
15 school, with 17 million of these girls never expected to attend school in their lifetimes; and
